post_text: During Morning Meetings, Mrs Nelson's Crew has begun learning patterns with beanbags. Moving the beanbag from side-to-side and top-to-bottom crosses the midlines of our bodies, and helps form stronger connections in our brains! Students have demonstrated EFFORT when focusing independently to learn new patterns. Students have also shown COLLABORATION when passing the beanbags as pairs. Washing hands and spacing around our classroom has kept this partner activity one that we can safely enjoy!

**AT HOME LEARNING STUDENTS WANTING SCHOOL LUNCH** a parent or gardian must complete a meal request daily through the following link by 9:00 AM to ensure their student gets a meal that day. This link can also be found on our website under the Students tab under Food & Nutrition.

Please notice that there is a separate link for Monday-Wednesday meals and a separate link for Thursday-Friday meals.

Each meal WILL include lunch and breakfast for the next day if selected.

Friday meals will be picked up during the regular lunch pick up on Thursday and must be requested no later than Thursday morning by 9:00 AM.

Meals will be picked up in front of the school on the south-east end of the building at 11:45 AM each day.

post_text:
ONLINE LEARNERS-Google Classroom is Ready!!!

Hello parents!

We have wonderful news! Google Classroom is working. Our wonderful IT personnel, figured out the error and has it up and going.

For information on how to log into your student‚Äôs email, please see your email that was sent to you today.

There should be an email from your online teacher in your student‚Äôs inbox. This will contain a link directly to our google classroom. By clicking it, your student will be added to the classroom.

If your student does not have an email in their inbox. Go to Google Classroom and log in there. On the main page of your student's google classroom, there will be a "join" option.

Your student needs to do this before school starts on Wednesday, August 19th.

Please let your online teachers know if you have any questions or problems.They are so excited to meet your student tomorrow!

With Davis County announcing their new A/B schedule we know that many of you have questions regarding what the 2020-2021 school year will look like for your family at Voyage.

We wanted to let you know that the Board of Directors and Administration of Voyage are reviewing our current plan for the 2020-20201 school year that will best facilitate the safety and education of children.

Please watch your email for information regarding the 2020-2021 school year. We will be sending updates as soon as they become available. Until that time, we ask for your patience and support.

Just a reminder that if you have not completed the Learning Option Survey the deadline is THIS Thursday, July 30th.

To complete the survey, please click on the following link: https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/VoyageAcademyLearningOptionSurvey2020

If you do no respond to the survey by this Thursday, your student will be enrolled at Voyage Academy for the in-person learning option.

If you have questions regarding our Reopening Plan, documents can be found on our website under the COVID Plan & Info tab.

Thank you for your promptness in completing this survey. This will allow the school to finalize plans for the 2020-2021 School Year.

post_text:
Teacher Spotlight of the Day!

Kristin Marietti, Second Grade

I absolutely love being a teacher. It was my dream as a little girl and my dream came true. The best thing about being a teacher is watching others improve themselves little by little, one day at a time. It's such a beautiful thing to be a part of.

I have an amazing class this year. They are full of love and dedication. I have watched this year as my class has overcome many obstacles.They are such an amazing group of 2nd graders. They also give the best hugs. I miss their hugs.

While I've been in quarantine I have enjoyed reading more books, playing board games and being with my dogs. One thing I have appreciated more while being in quarantine is the peace that I feel in the many quiet moments I experience. I am more aware of my childrens laughter, the bird singing, and the breeze blowing through an open window. These moments remind me that it's okay. Things will be okay.

Some fun facts about me are I LOVE dogs, I enjoy playing the piano, and I really like to bake. But I LOVE my family and my students most of all!!!

This year I have loved how loving the kids are. They are all willing to help out during any situation and they care about each other.

Erica Sperry

Learning from funny, thoughtful, kind, & creative little humans. They have the best ideas and say some pretty funny things.

This group of kids has a big heart. We had three new students this year and they instantly took them in. Also, they pretend to love my singing and think I am funny.

Something she has learned or enjoyed doing while in quarantine is...

Being outside when the sun is out!

Teacher Spotlight of the Day!

Kristy Culpepper, Third Grade

Kristy‚Äôs favorite thing about being a teacher is‚Ä¶

I love the kids and helping them grow. They are fun to be around and always (almost always) bring a smile to my face, even on my gloomiest day.

One thing she loves most about her class this year is‚Ä¶

I have a really good group of students this year. They are funny and kind; everyone gets along with each other.

Something she has learned or enjoyed doing while in quarantine is‚Ä¶

I have learned how to teach distantly (haha!) I have also learned that I need my classroom and my students, maybe more than they need me. I have enjoyed just being home with my own kids and spending more time with them.

3 fun facts or favorite things‚Ä¶

I love to hike, especially if it‚Äôs to a waterfall.

I like to write, and maybe one day will write the book that‚Äôs been in my head for a couple years now.

I am a huge baseball fan. I love the Atlanta Braves, but I enjoy watching any baseball game. I‚Äôm more invested in them when it is one of my own children or students playing.

post_text:
Student Council was given the opportunity to attend Charter Day on the Hill. What an awesome experience it was for them.

The Governor and gubernatorial candidates will be speaking to the students this day.
This event, held during National School Choice Week (January 26-February 1), it promotes choice in education and Utah's public charter schools. Administrators, teachers, students, and legislators come together to discuss the issues pertinent to public charter schools. Students get a first hand look at government in action through meeting with their legislator and capitol tours.

In an effort to share all of the amazing things happening at Voyage Academy, we will be sponsoring a photo contest. All participants will have a chance of winning a $100 gift card!

To enter, post a picture of your student doing something they love at Voyage. You may also post a photo, without your student, with a comment of why they love Voyage Academy. Pictures can be posted on Instagram and/or Facebook daily. Pictures must include the hashtag ‚Äú#VoyageAcademy‚Äù for the entry to be included in our contest. Post often and help spread the word until our closing date of Friday, January 24th! Every entry posted with #VoyageAcademy will receive an entry into the Photo Contest.

Open Enrollment for future students will open TODAY, Monday, January 6th! Encourage new students to enroll through sharing all of the wonderful things that take place at our amazing school. Please remember that enrollment for current students and their incoming siblings will happen in the Spring.

Thank you! We have attached a flyer with details.

post_text:
Due to the large response for our Grams and Gramps luncheon, we have had to make adjustments to our lunch times to accommodate numbers. The following are times for grandparents to join students for lunch. Please note that these times have changed and please notify grandparents who will be joining us:
1st Grade: 10:50 AM
2nd Grade: 11:10 AM
3rd Grade: 11:30 AM
4th Grade: 11:50 AM
5th Grade: 12:05 PM
6th Grade: 12:20 PM
Please have grandparents arrive early enough to allow them to have a badge printed and for the office to call down any additional siblings so that families can eat together. If grandparents are coming to eat with your student, please encourage your students to let their teacher know that they are expecting them. Thank you!

post_text: It's winter.... still!!! Voyage Academy would like to remind parents to plan extra time for the walk or drive to school in the morning. post_text: Voyage Academy has attended the International Safe School Conference for the past three years. The school‚Äôs safety committee has implemented many safety measures as a result of this conference. In October the school received the prestigious Gate Keeper Award for all the safety measures the school has in place. The school was selected from several school districts and charter schools throughout the U.S. and Canada. Voyage will continue to put measures in place to keep our students safe! A big thank you to the Clinton PD, Clinton City Fire Department, staff members, and parents for the role they played in helping us to achieve this accomplishment. (An email was sent to parents today detailing all of the safety measures that have been put into place) üòä

post_text:
Spread the word!

Friday, October 5th from 4:00 to 7:00 PM is our Annual Voyage Academy Fall Carnival!!

Come and join us for a fun night!! There is no entry fee for the Fall Carnival. There will be a silent auction. We will have a rock wall, bounce house, train, face painting, Dartside, big bowling, and a variety of food trucks. This year in addition to what we have had each grade has also come up with a game which includes a dunk tank where students will be able to dunk their teachers, candy walk, Digging for Gold, etc. Come and visit your past and current teachers at their game booth! 10 free games will also be available. It will be a fun time for the whole family!! You do not have to be a student at Voyage Academy to join in the fun!

Ticket prices the night of the carnival will be 4 for $1.00. Students can also turn in 5 box tops in exchange for 1 carnival ticket.

Here is a sneak peak to some of our silent auction items.

post_text: Our Annual Boo to the Flu Clinic on Monday, October 1st from 3:00 to 7:00 PM at Voyage Academy!! Voyage Academy was recently able to celebrate our 5-year anniversary. Many fantastic individuals helped prepare and put on a celebration of success for the school. We would like to give a round of applause to our student council and choir members who put on a stellar program. Becky Mortensen and Amy Mills that helped plan and organize the event with detailed consideration. Many local and state officials took time out of their day to attend and offer their ongoing support to Voyage. Thank you to our school board, administration, teachers, staff, students and parents for five wonderful years. We look forward to the continued success of the school thanks to the dedication of our Voyage family.

post_text: The 4th graders expedition has been all about rocks, minerals, fossils and soil. They had their Celebration of Learning where they held their very own 5th annual rock show. They shared their knowledge about the many rocks and minerals found in Utah. They also showcased their learning through writing realistic fiction narratives about a rock traveling through the rock cycle. Fourth graders LOVE rocks.

post_text: Nutritious free meals are available for children ages 18 and younger at many Utah locations throughout the summer while school is out of session. For available locations visit the USDA website at https://www.fns.usda.gov/summerfoodrocks or contact the Utah State Board of Education, Child Nutrition Programs at 801-538-7680. Information can also be found on the Utah State Board of Education website https://schools.utah.gov/cnp/sfsp
